+# ION Portable Package Specification
+
+Status: `DRAFT_V0_1`
+
+## Purpose
+
+The ION Portable package is a user-held continuity body for a project,
+company, research effort, or long-running AI collaboration.
+
+It is designed for the simplest demo:
+
+```text
+fresh ION GPT chat
+→ upload project files
+→ receive project memory pack
+→ continue later by uploading latest pack
+```
+
+## Required Top-Level Files
+
+```text
+MANIFEST.json
+README_START_HERE.md
+PROJECT_BRIEF.md
+CURRENT_STATE.md
+SOURCE_MAP.yaml
+DECISION_LEDGER.md
+OPEN_QUESTIONS.md
+NEXT_ACTIONS.md
+RISKS_AND_ASSUMPTIONS.md
+USER_PREFERENCES.md
+```
+
+## Required Folders
+
+```text
+context/
+receipts/
+diffs/
+friction/
+exports/
+raw_index/
+```
+
+## State Boundary
+
+The package is user-held continuity, not production state.
+
+AI output becomes package state only when:
+
+```text
+proposal → user acceptance → receipt → package update
+```
+
+## Package Size Guidance
+
+Keep packages small and text-forward. Prefer markdown, json, yaml, and csv.
+Summarize huge source files instead of blindly copying them.
+
+## Inheritance Rule
+
+A future chat should inherit from:
+
+1. latest manifest
+2. latest receipt
+3. current state
+4. decision ledger
+5. active context package
+6. next actions
+7. source map
+8. friction ledger

