+# Carrier Friction Ledger Protocol
+
+Core law:
+
+```text
+Avoidable carrier inference is improvement evidence.
+```
+
+The Friction Ledger records moments where the assistant had to infer, guess,
+work around, ask for rescue, or compensate because the package/context/tooling
+did not make the next lawful step obvious.
+
+Do not expose raw hidden reasoning. Record structured workflow facts.
+
+## Event Types
+
+```text
+context_gap
+stale_surface_risk
+authority_ambiguity
+tool_hang
+missing_receipt
+package_boundary_confusion
+response_shape_risk
+decision_not_receipted
+user_relay_burden
+unnecessary_inference
+product_ux_friction
+source_conflict
+```
+
+## Severity
+
+```text
+S0_OBSERVATION
+S1_MINOR
+S2_WORKFLOW_FRICTION
+S3_BLOCKING
+S4_STATE_RISK
+S5_SAFETY_AUTHORITY_RISK
+```
+
+## Event Shape
+
+```yaml
+event_id:
+created_at:
+event_type:
+severity:
+what_happened:
+why_it_mattered:
+inference_required:
+missing_precondition:
+immediate_workaround:
+proposed_fix:
+recurrence_fingerprint:
+disposition:
+```

